                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <head>222. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d222fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 330.13/6–457. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_niact1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Drafted by <persName>Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-06-04T17:11:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1957—5:11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8467. Eyes only for <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> from
                    Secretary. I feel your memorandum to Soviet Delegation of May 31 exceeded your
                    authority both as to substance and procedure. We are urgently considering here
                    what to do about it and you will get further guidance tomorrow morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
